notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T11:59:36.846Z",codex-agent,"Normalization policy v1: (1) exact duplicate titles are resolved to one canonical wording plus explicit archival wording for superseded peers; (2) near-duplicate run/alert/PR tracking items are treated as intentional series when differentiated by run number/date/alert id/PR id; (3) active non-terminal items must not self-parent and must follow Feature->Epic and Task/Issue/Chore->Feature|Epic parent rules; (4) terminal historical self-parent lineage is preserved unless needed for deterministic active-work selection."
